article_summary:
So perhaps Friday’s official Department of Labor report is unlikely to deliver the full Blutarsky.
The ADP/Moody’s survey this week estimated October job gains of 182,000 for all private payrolls and found relative strength in small-business hiring.
Could the economy really be that bad?
“Reported job creation came to a halt in October, with owners adding a net 0.0 workers per firm in recent months,” according to the latest small-business survey from the National Federation of Independent Business, due out later today.
The zero-point-zero reading matches John Blutarsky’s grade point average from Faber College.
